:R-HSA-427652  a            obo:GO_0035435 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Phosphorus is an essential element that is critical for structural and metabolic roles in all living organisms. Cells obtain phosphorus in the form of negatively-charged inorganic phosphate (Pi). Two SLC families transport phosphate in mammals; SLC34 (Murer H et al, 2004) and SLC20 (Collins JF et al, 2004). Both are secondary-active, Na+-coupled transporter systems which use the inward Na+ gradient (from the Na+-K+-ATPase) to drive phosphate influx into cells (Virkki LV et al, 2007)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Sodium-coupled phosphate cotransporters" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: D'Eustachio, Peter, 2025-08-12" , "Authored: Jassal, Bijay, 2009-06-23" , "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2009-06-23" , "Reviewed: He, L, 2009-08-24" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-427652" ;
